<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">23</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">the other descendants of their forefathers.  But to return to my purpose, I shall begin with Greenland.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The Greenlanders adorn their necks, arms and ears, with beads, corals, pendants and bracelets of black skins set with pearls.  They also embellish their persons by staining their foreheads, chins, arms, legs and thighs with black streaks indented in the skin by means of a needle and coloured thread &#8211; the women are hard favoured, sluttish and filthy, especially those who had children &#8211; sometimes the Greenlanders eat their meal raw, sometimes they boil it, or dry it in the sun and wind &#8211; Wives submit to chastisement from their husbands with great resignation.  After the birth of an infant the Mother is swathed around the belly with a broad belt <span class="AddHand-author">And next day returns to her usual occupations</span> &#8211; she always carries a child at her back even while she is at labour, and sometimes suckles it to the third or fourth year.</p>

